# Middleware

## Session refresh

`src/middleware.ts` delegates to `updateSession()` in `lib/supabase/middleware.ts`.

- Refresh Supabase auth cookies on every matched request
- Matcher excludes static assets and images
- Do not add business logic here — keep middleware fast

## Route protection

- Public: `/`, `/login`, `/signup`, `/auth/callback`
- Protected: everything under `/(dashboard)/`
- Redirect unauthenticated users to `/login` with `?next=` return URL

## Supabase SSR pattern

- Use `@supabase/ssr` cookie helpers — never store tokens in localStorage
- `createServerClient` in middleware with `getAll` / `setAll` cookie methods
- Server and client factories must use the same cookie config

## Do not

- Call external APIs from middleware
- Parse or trust custom auth headers without validation
- Skip session refresh to "optimize" — stale sessions break RLS
